The Foreign Ministers of France, Jordan and Egypt call for an immediate and permanent ceasefire in Gaza and the release of all hostages held by Palestinian militants. Speaking at a joint press conference in Cairo, French diplomacy leader Stéphane Séjourné> said that his government will present a draft resolution to the United Nations Security Council that defines a "political" solution of the war. The text, he explained, will present "all criteria for a solution to two states» of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, the peace project long supported by the international community but opposed by the Israeli government of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu>.
